{
  "title": [
    "slide~"
  ],
  "description": "smooth signals logarithmically",
  "origin": "cyclone",
  "categories": [
    "Envelopes and LFOs"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "signal to smooth out"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "slide up value in samples"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "slide down value in samples"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "smoothed signal"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "initial slide up value in samples",
      "default": "1"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "initial slide down value in samples",
      "default": "1"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "slide_down <float>",
      "description": "set the slide down value"
    },
    {
      "type": "slide_up <float>",
      "description": "set the slide up value"
    },
    {
      "type": "reset",
      "description": "sets the current output sample value to 0"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[slide~] filters an input signal logarithmically between changes in signal value. The formula is: y(n) = y(n-1) + ((x(n) - y(n-1))/slide).\nDifferent than [rampsmooth~], [slide~] will smooth audio transitions in a non linear way. It's also useful for envelope following and lowpass filtering."
}